## 2. Core Architecture (Track A)

### 2.1 Truth Hierarchy (three-signal interface)

Track A only acts through a strict hierarchy. No signal may do two jobs.

| Signal | Value | Role |
|--------|-------|------|
| **Macro Regime (WHY)** | BULLISH / BEARISH | Worldview gate — not an entry signal |
| **Execution Pulses (WHAT)** | BUY / SELL | Tactical proposals — no authority alone |
| **Position Truth (REALITY)** | LONG / SHORT / FLAT | Exchange-sourced ground truth — always vetoes inference |

> **Reality overrides belief. Always.**

Until the macro regime is known, ORIC waits. Waiting is discipline, not inactivity.

### 2.2 Symbol isolation

Each symbol runs with isolated runtime state (separate process or fully isolated runtime object) to prevent cross-contamination through:

- stale orders
- drifted trackers
- exceptions propagating across symbols
- precision/step-size mismatch

### 2.3 Exchange and data layer

- CCXT for market data and orders.
- Exchange truth is periodically re-read (positions + open orders) — never assumed or cached as final.

